correction_response: This tweet is potentially misleading. As of November 2021, the full vaccination rate in New York City is around 70%, not over 90%. While it's great news that there were no reported COVID-related deaths on that day, it's important to accurately represent the vaccination rate to avoid false security.
note_1_text: Data after a holiday almost always under reports actuals. NYC's own dashboard warns about recent data lag (https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data.page#aboutthedata). 7-day averages are much more reliable.    Also, the 90% rate is incorrect. 88.5% of adults and 76.5% of all residents have at least one dose (https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data-vaccines.page#people).
note_2_text: The claim that there were no COVID-19 related deaths on 11/29/21 in New York City can not be stated as fact according to NYC’s Health Dept website. https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data.page    The claim of 90% vaccination rate for NYC is false https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data-vaccines.page
